&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/role/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/role/> ;
  schema:name "Role" ;
  schema:description "A Role is a triple (Σ, N, ⪯) — a capability signature Σ specifying the minimum operations any bearer must provide, a norm-set N of role-indexed obligations and permissions that apply to any bearer, and a subsumption position ⪯ in the preorder of all roles ordered by signature inclusion. The defining structure: a role is a bearer-independent normative interface type — the deontic and capability profile that any agent must satisfy to count as filling it. Three projections of the same structure: a role as capability specification (Σ), as norm bundle (N), and as positional node in a role hierarchy (⪯). A role persists when vacant; its norms apply to any and every bearer; no role is constituted by its current occupant." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-18" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-18" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/role/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Agent, Officer, Office, Norm, HohfeldianPosition, NormativeSystem, Institution, Duty, Incumbent, CapabilitySignature" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/role/> .

